prvtCfmMib.name: prvtCfmMib

revisions.description: Add posibility to enable/disable 1wJitter, 2wJitter, FrameLoss and Latency on a CFM profile.
Fixed some minor description issues, removed prvtCfmProfileFrameLossBucketSize
Added prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmSuccessRate, prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmMinTime, prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmAvgTime, prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmMaxTime, prvtCfmLbrBadMsdu.

prvtCfmMib.contactinfo: BATM/Telco Systems Support team Email: For North America: techsupport@telco.com For North Europe: support@batm.de, info@batm.de For the rest of the world: techsupport@telco.com
prvtCfmMib.description: Prvt extension of Connectivity Fault Management module for managing IEEE 802.1ag

prvtCfmUpdateInterval.name: prvtCfmUpdateInterval
prvtCfmUpdateInterval.description: Time between monitoring parameters update (in seconds). A value of 0 suspends the monitoring task and a value different from 0 resumes it. Default is 20 seconds.

prvtCfmProfileTableNextIndex.name: prvtCfmProfileTableNextIndex
prvtCfmProfileTableNextIndex.description: This object contains an unused value for prvtCfmProfileIndex in the prvtCfmProfileTable, or a zero to indicate that none exist.

prvtCfmProfileTable.name: prvtCfmProfileTable
prvtCfmProfileTable.description: Table contains loopback results from all remote MEPs in the MA.

prvtCfmProfileRate.name: prvtCfmProfileRate
prvtCfmProfileRate.description: Number of Request packets to send each time.

prvtCfmProfileSize.name: prvtCfmProfileSize
prvtCfmProfileSize.description: Size of data TLV included in probe packets (in octets).

prvtCfmProfileBucketSize.name: prvtCfmProfileBucketSize
prvtCfmProfileBucketSize.description: Number of the results to save for results calculation.

prvtCfmProfile1wJitterError.name: prvtCfmProfile1wJitterError
prvtCfmProfile1wJitterError.description: Specifies one-way jitter error values to monitor in milliseconds.

prvtCfmProfile1wJitterWarning.name: prvtCfmProfile1wJitterWarning
prvtCfmProfile1wJitterWarning.description: Specifies one-way jitter warning values to monitor in milliseconds.

prvtCfmProfileJitterError.name: prvtCfmProfileJitterError
prvtCfmProfileJitterError.description: Specifies round-trip jitter error values to monitor in milliseconds.

prvtCfmProfileJitterErrorPeriod.name: prvtCfmProfileJitterErrorPeriod
prvtCfmProfileJitterErrorPeriod.description: Specifies the duration jitter occurs in seconds.

prvtCfmProfileJitterWarning.name: prvtCfmProfileJitterWarning
prvtCfmProfileJitterWarning.description: Specifies round-trip jitter warning values to monitor in milliseconds. If set value is greater than the jitter-error it means that the warning is disabled.

prvtCfmProfileJitterWarningPeriod.name: prvtCfmProfileJitterWarningPeriod
prvtCfmProfileJitterWarningPeriod.description: Specifies the duration jitter occurs in seconds.

prvtCfmProfileFrameLossError.name: prvtCfmProfileFrameLossError
prvtCfmProfileFrameLossError.description: Specifies round-trip frame-loss error values to monitor. The default is frame-loss of 10% is reported.

prvtCfmProfileFrameLossWarning.name: prvtCfmProfileFrameLossWarning
prvtCfmProfileFrameLossWarning.description: Specifies round-trip frame-loss warning values to monitor. The default is frame-loss of 8% is reported. If set value is greater than the frame-loss-error it means that the warning is disable.

prvtCfmProfileLatencyError.name: prvtCfmProfileLatencyError
prvtCfmProfileLatencyError.description: Specifies round-trip latency error values to monitor in milliseconds.

prvtCfmProfileLatencyErrorPeriod.name: prvtCfmProfileLatencyErrorPeriod
prvtCfmProfileLatencyErrorPeriod.description: Specifies the duration latency increase occurs in seconds.

prvtCfmProfileLatencyWarning.name: prvtCfmProfileLatencyWarning
prvtCfmProfileLatencyWarning.description: Specifies round-trip latency error values to monitor in milliseconds. If set value is greater than the latency-error it means that the warning is disabled.

prvtCfmProfileLatencyWarningPeriod.name: prvtCfmProfileLatencyWarningPeriod
prvtCfmProfileLatencyWarningPeriod.description: Specifies the duration latency increase occurs in seconds.

prvtCfmProfileRowStatus.name: prvtCfmProfileRowStatus
prvtCfmProfileRowStatus.description: The status of the row. The writable columns in a row can not be changed if the row is active. All columns must have a valid value before a row can be activated.

prvtCfmProfile1wJitterEnable.name: prvtCfmProfile1wJitterEnable
prvtCfmProfile1wJitterEnable.description: A boolean showing if one way jitter calculation is enabled.

prvtCfmProfileJitterEnable.name: prvtCfmProfileJitterEnable
prvtCfmProfileJitterEnable.description: A boolean showing if two way jitter calculation is enabled.

prvtCfmProfileFrameLossEnable.name: prvtCfmProfileFrameLossEnable
prvtCfmProfileFrameLossEnable.description: A boolean showing if frame loss calculation is enabled.

prvtCfmProfileLatencyEnable.name: prvtCfmProfileLatencyEnable
prvtCfmProfileLatencyEnable.description: A boolean showing if latency calculation is enabled.

prvtCfmProcessTableNextIndex.name: prvtCfmProcessTableNextIndex
prvtCfmProcessTableNextIndex.description: This object contains an unused value for prvtCfmProcessIndex in the prvtCfmProcessTable, or a zero to indicate that none exists.

prvtCfmProcessTable.name: prvtCfmProcessTable
prvtCfmProcessTable.description: Private extension of dot1agCfmMaNetTable. Controls the two-way monitoring process for MEP's in the MA.

prvtCfmProcessProfileIndex.name: prvtCfmProcessProfileIndex
prvtCfmProcessProfileIndex.description: Index of the monitoring profile to be used.

prvtCfmProcessName.name: prvtCfmProcessName
prvtCfmProcessName.description: The name of the process. Should be unique per domain/MA

prvtCfmProcessStatus.name: prvtCfmProcessStatus
prvtCfmProcessStatus.description: Enable/disable two-way monitoring process for MEP's in the MA.

prvtCfmProcessRepeatInterval.name: prvtCfmProcessRepeatInterval
prvtCfmProcessRepeatInterval.description: Repeating frequency of the monitoring process.

prvtCfmProcessPacketType.name: prvtCfmProcessPacketType
prvtCfmProcessPacketType.description: Use CFM Loopback or Y.1731 LMMs and DMMs packets.

prvtCfmProcessUnreturnedPkts.name: prvtCfmProcessUnreturnedPkts
prvtCfmProcessUnreturnedPkts.description: Number of requests for which a reply hasn't been received. These packets will be counted as lost when they enter timeout.

prvtCfmProcessRowStatus.name: prvtCfmProcessRowStatus
prvtCfmProcessRowStatus.description: The status of the row. The writable columns in a row can not be changed if the row is active. All columns must have a valid value before a row can be activated.

prvtCfmProcessResultOneWayJitter.name: prvtCfmProcessResultOneWayJitter
prvtCfmProcessResultOneWayJitter.description: One way jitter calculated for a specific remote MEP in milliseconds

prvtCfmProcessResultTwoWayJitter.name: prvtCfmProcessResultTwoWayJitter
prvtCfmProcessResultTwoWayJitter.description: Two way jitter calculated for a specific remote MEP in milliseconds

prvtCfmProcessResultLatency.name: prvtCfmProcessResultLatency
prvtCfmProcessResultLatency.description: Two way latency calculated for a specific remote MEP in milliseconds

prvtCfmProcessResultFrameloss.name: prvtCfmProcessResultFrameloss
prvtCfmProcessResultFrameloss.description: Two way frameloss calculated for a specific remote MEP in units of hundredths of percent. Note: When prvtCfmProcessResultFrameloss has value of 10000, all the values of prvtCfmProcessResultOneWayJitter, prvtCfmProcessResultTwoWayJitter and prvtCfmProcessResultLatency are irrelevant.

prvtCfmMaTable.name: prvtCfmMaTable
prvtCfmMaTable.description: Table includes extra variables needed for Y.1731 support and service awareness

prvtCfmMaCompAisLckEnabled.name: prvtCfmMaCompAisLckEnabled
prvtCfmMaCompAisLckEnabled.description: Turn the AIS & LCK features on/off.

prvtCfmMaCompAisLckLevel.name: prvtCfmMaCompAisLckLevel
prvtCfmMaCompAisLckLevel.description: The MD level at which AIS & LCK frames will be sent. It should be greater then that of the current domain. The default value is '-1' representing 'not-configured'.

prvtCfmMaCompAisLckInterval.name: prvtCfmMaCompAisLckInterval
prvtCfmMaCompAisLckInterval.description: The time interval at which AIS and LCK frames will be sent

prvtCfmMaCompAisLckPriority.name: prvtCfmMaCompAisLckPriority
prvtCfmMaCompAisLckPriority.description: COS parameter for the outgoing AIS & LCK frames. The default value is '6'

prvtCfmMaCompServiceId.name: prvtCfmMaCompServiceId
prvtCfmMaCompServiceId.description: The primary service ID attached to this MA

prvtCfmMaCompNumberOfServices.name: prvtCfmMaCompNumberOfServices
prvtCfmMaCompNumberOfServices.description: The number of services attached to this MA

prvtCfmMaCompClearConnectivity.name: prvtCfmMaCompClearConnectivity
prvtCfmMaCompClearConnectivity.description: Number of MEP or 0 for all

prvtCfmMepAlarmSupressed.name: prvtCfmMepAlarmSupressed
prvtCfmMepAlarmSupressed.description: A boolean showing if an AIS or LCK packet was received from a lower level

prvtCfmMepAisCondition.name: prvtCfmMepAisCondition
prvtCfmMepAisCondition.description: A boolean showing if there is AIS condition. The value of the object is true (an AIS condition), when there is a detection of signal-fail condition at a Server layer or reception of AIS at a server (sub-) layer MEP [AIS condition/Rec. ITU-T Y.1731]. The AIS condition will exit when following criteria is met: During an interval equal to 3.5 times the AIS transmission period indicated in the AIS frames received earlier, the MEP does not receive AIS frames or, when ETH-CC is used, upon clearing of LOC defect at MEP /Appendix I/Rec. ITU-T Y.1731. If prvtCfmMaCompAisLckLevel is configured the MEP should send AIS packets.

prvtCfmMepLckCondition.name: prvtCfmMepLckCondition
prvtCfmMepLckCondition.description: A boolean showing if the MEP should lock the service towards the client and send LCK packets

prvtCfmMepAisLifetime.name: prvtCfmMepAisLifetime
prvtCfmMepAisLifetime.description: The lifetime of the last received AIS packet. During an interval equal to 3.5 times the AIS transmission period indicated in the AIS frames received earlier, the MEP does not receive AIS frames. The value is valid (non-zero) if AIS packets are being received.

prvtCfmMepLckLifetime.name: prvtCfmMepLckLifetime
prvtCfmMepLckLifetime.description: The lifetime of the last received LCK packet. During an interval equal to 3.5 times the LCK transmission period indicated in the LCK frames received earlier, the MEP does not receive LCK frames. The value is valid (non-zero) if AIS packets are being received.

prvtCfmMepTransmitMcastLbm.name: prvtCfmMepTransmitMcastLbm
prvtCfmMepTransmitMcastLbm.description: A boolean to control sending Y.1731 multicast loopback.

prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmInfinite.name: prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmInfinite
prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmInfinite.description: A boolean to control sending LBMs continuously until the operation is explicitly stopped by setting this back to false

prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmDelay.name: prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmDelay
prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmDelay.description: An amount of time to wait between sent LBMs (in seconds).

prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmTimeout.name: prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmTimeout
prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmTimeout.description: An amount of time to wait after the last sent LBM if no LBR is received (in seconds).

prvtCfmMepTransmitLtmTimeout.name: prvtCfmMepTransmitLtmTimeout
prvtCfmMepTransmitLtmTimeout.description: An amount of time to wait after the last sent LTM if no LTR is received (in seconds).

prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmSentPkts.name: prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmSentPkts
prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmSentPkts.description: Number of successfully sent packets in the current LBM session.

prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmSuccessRate.name: prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmSuccessRate
prvtCfmMepTransmitLbmSuccessRate.description: Success rate of the current LBM session (in percentage*100).

prvtCfmMepSuportedRemoteMepsNo.name: prvtCfmMepSuportedRemoteMepsNo
prvtCfmMepSuportedRemoteMepsNo.description: The number of suported remote meps (for TMarc3x0 and TMarc280 devices)

prvtCfmMepExcludeCCMTLV.name: prvtCfmMepExcludeCCMTLV
prvtCfmMepExcludeCCMTLV.description: Bitmask that specifies what TLVs should be excluded(for TMarc3x0 and TMarc280 devices): On set opertaion: BIT4 = MSB Include/Exclude bit - if it is 1 the tlv is excluded from the specific CCM packet, if it is 0 the tlv will be included in the specific CCM packet BIT3 = If set 1 the OrgSpecific TLV will be excluded or included BIT2 = If set 1 the InterfaceStatus TLV will be excluded or included BIT1 = If set 1 the PortStatus TLV will be excluded or included BIT0 = LSB If set 1 the Sender ID TLV will be excluded or included Examples: If Interface Status and Port Status will be excluded the bitmask will look like this: 16 in hexadecimal BIT4 BIT3 BIT2 BIT1 BIT0 1 0 1 1 0 If Interface Status and Port Status will be included the bitmask will look like this: 06 in hexadecimal BIT4 BIT3 BIT2 BIT1 BIT0 0 0 1 1 0 On get operation it shows the bits corresponding to the excluded tlvs If Interface Status and Port Status are excluded: 06 in hexadecimal - 0 1 1 0

prvtCfmLbrTable.name: prvtCfmLbrTable
prvtCfmLbrTable.description: Table contains loopback results following the last loopback operation.

prvtCfmLbrSeqNumber.name: prvtCfmLbrSeqNumber
prvtCfmLbrSeqNumber.description: Transaction identifier/Sequence number of the received LBR.

prvtCfmLbrReceiveOrder.name: prvtCfmLbrReceiveOrder
prvtCfmLbrReceiveOrder.description: An index to distinguish among multiple LBRs with the same LBR Transaction Identifier field value. This situation can appear in the case of multicast loopback.

prvtCfmLbrTime.name: prvtCfmLbrTime
prvtCfmLbrTime.description: Remote MEPs response time in milliseconds.

prvtCfmLbrMacAddress.name: prvtCfmLbrMacAddress
prvtCfmLbrMacAddress.description: Remote MEPs mac address. For unicast loopback this is the same as dot1agCfmMepTransmitLbmDestMacAddress, but for multicast loopback there will be different entries.

prvtCfmLbrBadMsdu.name: prvtCfmLbrBadMsdu
prvtCfmLbrBadMsdu.description: Result of the Data TLV verification.

prvtCfmLtrTable.name: prvtCfmLtrTable
prvtCfmLtrTable.description: This table adds the possibility to measure the response time to a linktrace request.

prvtCfmLtrTime.name: prvtCfmLtrTime
prvtCfmLtrTime.description: Remote MPs response time in milliseconds.

prvtCfmMaAisLckVlanTable.name: prvtCfmMaAisLckVlanTable
prvtCfmMaAisLckVlanTable.description: Table includes extra variables needed for AIS/LCK configurable vlans

prvtCfmMaAisLckVlanEntry.name: prvtCfmMaAisLckVlanEntry
prvtCfmMaAisLckVlanEntry.description: Table includes extra variables needed for AIS/LCK configurable vlans

prvtCfmMaAisLckVlanId.name: prvtCfmMaAisLckVlanId
prvtCfmMaAisLckVlanId.description: Vlan ID (towards customer level) that the generated AIS/LCK packets should use.

prvtCfm1wJitterThreshold.name: prvtCfm1wJitterThreshold
prvtCfm1wJitterThreshold.description: This trap should be sent whenever the one way jitter on a CFM test will surpass one of the 2 defined thresholds.

prvtCfmJitterThreshold.name: prvtCfmJitterThreshold
prvtCfmJitterThreshold.description: This trap should be sent whenever the two way jitter on a CFM test will surpass one of the 2 defined thresholds.

prvtCfmFrameLossThreshold.name: prvtCfmFrameLossThreshold
prvtCfmFrameLossThreshold.description: This trap should be sent whenever the frame loss on a CFM test will surpass one of the 2 defined thresholds.

prvtCfmLatencyThreshold.name: prvtCfmLatencyThreshold
prvtCfmLatencyThreshold.description: This trap should be sent whenever the latency on a CFM test will surpass one of the 2 defined thresholds.

prvtCfmAisReceived.name: prvtCfmAisReceived
prvtCfmAisReceived.description: This trap is issued whenever an AIS condition with specified lifetime on a MEP is met.

prvtCfmLckReceived.name: prvtCfmLckReceived
prvtCfmLckReceived.description: This trap is issued whenever an LCK condition with specified lifetime on a MEP is met.
